   January 30, 2002         DOL > Interactive Tools

   Interactive Tools


                                          On This Page



                                            * Compliance Assistance Tools
                                            * Employment & Unemployment
                                            * Educational & Learning Tools
                                            * Career Tools
                                            * Safety Tools

   Looking for the job of your dreams? Want to find out the latest
   employment statistics? Thinking of continuing your education? Our
   interactive tools use the power of the Web to bring you electronic
   services.

   Compliance Assistance Tools
     * elaws: Employment Laws Assistance for Workers and Small Businesses
       Advisors help you understand your rights and responsibilities under
       the employment laws and regulations administered by the Department
       of Labor.
     * The Small Business Compliance Assistance Information Inventory
       Matrix is a matrix of Department of Labor Compliance Assistance
       materials available on the Internet.
     * Safety & Health eTools
     * OSHA Inspection Data

   Employment & Unemployment
     * Selective Access is a survey-specific database query tool where the
       user selects from options available for any individual survey, and
       the appropriate data series are retrieved. Year ranges and output
       options are chosen by the user.
     * The Series Report application provides experienced users of Bureau
       of Labor Statistics (BLS) data with the quickest form of access to
       timeseries data.
     * Most Requested Statistics is a set of lists from which users select
       the most popular data statistics, range of years to be retrieved,
       and an output format.

   Educational & Learning Tools
     * America's Learning eXchange connects you to career development,
       training and education, and employment resources important to
       remain competitive in today's multi-dimensional workforce.
     * Calculate your money's value using the Inflation Calculator
       available from the Bureau of Labor Statistics home page and the
       Consumer Price Index page.

   Career Tools
     * Find your first or next job using America's Job Bank.
     * Explore hundreds of careers using America's Career InfoNet.
     * O*Net, the Occupational Information Network, makes occupational
       information interactive and accessible for all.

   Safety Tools
     * The Mine Safety and Health Administration (MSHA) Data Retrieval
       System permits miners, operators, and other interested parties to
       retrieve mine overviews, accident histories, violation histories,
       inspector dust samplings, and operator dust samplings.
     * Search Mine Fatality Reports from the Mine Safety and Health
       Administration (MSHA)
     * Use the Occupational Safety and Health Administration's (OSHA)
       Online Complaint Form to file complaints about workplace safety and
       health hazards.
     * Safety & Health eTools


